The defendant Christopher M Sekorski was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Christopher M Sekorski is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Christopher M Sekorski was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Repeater, Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Laura Gruen: makes statement 
Keller: this is a case where we can't prove everything that was charged and those charges were dismissed outright. There are treatment needs present and some history - they are fighting to have a better life. There should be some penalty. It's clear that there was a disturbance and it was domestic in nature and some neighbors witnessed it. There should be some accountability. 
O'Neill: They have been togther 3.5 yrs and they both have AODA issues. This is a close case for probation and the use of their resources when he's been doing fine over the past 9 mos. 
Def: Life has been going a lot better since we both stopped drinking. Our relationship has improved since then.
